Step 1: Identify the relevant numbers from the statements.
• From the balance sheet, the Total Assets at the beginning (2023-12-31) is 28,000,000.00 and at the end (2024-02-05) is 30,858,088.75.
• From the income statement, the Total Revenue is 20,318,450.67.

Step 2: Compute the Average Total Assets.
Average Total Assets = (Beginning Total Assets + Ending Total Assets) / 2  
= (28,000,000.00 + 30,858,088.75) / 2  
= 58,858,088.75 / 2  
= 29,429,044.375

Step 3: Calculate the Total Asset Turnover Ratio.
Total Asset Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Total Assets  
= 20,318,450.67 / 29,429,044.375  
≈ 0.69

Thus, the Total Asset Turnover Ratio is approximately 0.69.
